    "narrative": "Today\u2019s lineup for the Austin Waves is headlined by **Gunnar Henderson**, who registers an elite 81.88 score. He is the clear must-start, benefiting from a massive +16% park factor and a favorable matchup against Houser. We are also banking on **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (67.80) and **Marcell Ozuna** (66.28) to provide the middle-of-the-order thump; **Marcell Ozuna** specifically gains significant value from wind-out conditions, pushing his upside well into the strong category. **Miguel Vargas** remains a high-floor play at 64.07, leveraging wind-aided conditions and a top-of-the-order promotion to maximize his scoring potential.\n\nOur bench strategy was dictated by the scarcity of stolen bases and general efficiency, leading to the difficult omission of **Coby Mayo**. While **Coby Mayo** (54.50) benefits from the same hitter-friendly environment as **Gunnar Henderson**, he was edged out by the superior plate appearance security of **Drake Baldwin** and **Jorge Polanco**. We are keeping a close watch on **Jackson Merrill** (58.20); while his matchup against Freeland is technically a \"strong\" start, the 39% rain risk creates a volatile floor. Additionally, managing the risk of Jacob deGrom remains a priority. While **Kyle Tucker** (57.87) is an automatic start despite the SP skill penalty, **Andy Pages** (43.59) sits at the absolute bottom of our efficiency threshold; he remains in the lineup only for his potential to swipe a bag against a pitcher prone to allowing steals, but he is at high risk of being moved to the bench if further caps-preservation is required.",
